From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 15:05:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Use a stable DualSense mono speaker endpoint id.

Spider-Man Remastered keeps a controller speaker endpoint cached across
controller changes. The physical Pulse sink names differ between the standard
DualSense and DualSense Edge controllers, so using the raw Pulse sink name as
the Wine endpoint id strands the cached app-side endpoint after a model swap.

Expose the controller mono speaker with the same app-facing endpoint id used by
the standard DualSense Pulse sink while still routing streams to the currently
connected physical DualSense speaker sink in winepulse. Unplug still removes
the old physical device; the next plug creates a new physical Pulse sink, but
the app-facing controller speaker identity stays stable enough for cached
effect-output clients to resolve to the new device.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 22222222222..33333333333 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -1251,11 +1251,17 @@ static BOOL pulse_stream_dualsense_mono_format(const struct pulse_stream *stream
     return stream->dataflow == eRender && stream->ss.channels == 1;
 }
 
+#define DUALSENSE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID \
+    "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_Wireless_Controller-00.Default__Speaker__sink"
+
 static BOOL pulse_set_endpoint_id(PhysDevice *dev)
 {
     unsigned int generation;
     size_t len;
 
+    if (is_dualsense_speaker_sink(dev))
+        return !!(dev->endpoint_id = strdup(DUALSENSE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID));
+
     if (!is_dualsense_audio_device(dev) || (dev->flow == eRender && !dev->raw_haptic_target
             && strstr(dev->pulse_name, "Speaker__sink")))
         return !!(dev->endpoint_id = strdup(dev->pulse_name));
